A 23-year-old man was stoned to death in Mathopestad near Boons outside Rustenburg, North West police said on Monday. Lieutenant Colonel Pelonomi Makau said on Saturday an altercation ensued after a 41-year-old man allegedly groped the younger man s girlfriend. The incident led to a fight and the 41-year-old man was stabbed with a knife in the neck. Makau said after the man was stabbed, his friends joined the fight and pelted the 23-year-old with stones. They left the 23-year-old unconscious. Both men were taken to the hospital, where the 23-year-old was declared dead on arrival. The 41-year-old was then arrested and is expected to appear in the Koster Magistrate s Court on Tuesday, Malau said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.